Package biz.littlej.jreqs.predicates

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Predicate<T>
    Determines a boolean value for a given input.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AllInstanceOfPredicate
    Checks that all input objects are instances of the specified class.
    AndPredicate<T>
    Returns a predicate that evaluates to true if all specified predicates also do for the same input, like the logical AND.
    AssignableFromPredicate
    Checks that all input classes are assignable from the input class.
    EqualToPredicate<T>
    Checks if an input object is equal to the specified object, using Objects.equals(java.lang.Object, java.lang.Object).
    InstanceOfPredicate
    Checks that the input object is an instance of the specified class.
    IterableElementsPredicate
    Applies a predicate to all elements of the specified Collection.
    OrPredicate<T>
    Returns a predicate that evaluates to true if any of the specified predicates also do for the same input, like the logical OR.
    PatternContainedPredicate
    Checks if the input CharSequence matches the specified Pattern.
    PredicateOperations
    Some predicates that evaluate to a boolean logic operation on other predicates' evaluations.
    Predicates
    Static utility methods that provide Predicate instances.
    XorPredicate<T>
    Returns a predicate that evaluates to true if at exactly one of the specified predicates also does for the same input, like the logical XOR.
